id: pm-hib1
title: "Point-in-time read projection: pm get --at <version|timestamp> renders reconstructed historical item state without mutating"
description: Expose SDK and CLI point-in-time item reads that reconstruct verified historical state by version or timestamp without mutating or locking the tracker.
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,history,immutable-record
created_at: "2026-07-06T23:18:28.374Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T06:46:35.673Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-14T06:44:42.952Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "pm get <id> --at <version> and --at <timestamp> return the reconstructed state with reconstructed:true and as_of_* fields in both json and toon; reconstruction reuses the restore replay helper (single implementation, verified by test); invalid/future targets fail with a structured error listing the valid version range; SDK exposes the same primitive with reference docs; works after history-compact (checkpoint-aware replay); no mutation, no lock, no history entry is written by the read"
parent: pm-o2kc
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: Added immutable getItemAt/readHistory SDK APIs and pm get --at on a shared verified replay kernel with explicit strict-read and at-or-before restore policies.
expected_result: "Historical item states are inspectable by version or timestamp without locks, writes, or history mutations, including after compaction."
actual_result: "CLI and SDK return immutable marked historical projections; historical reads preserve item history and the context-usage ledger byte-for-byte, get rejects future timestamps, and restore retains at-or-before semantics with command-specific diagnostics."
